################################################################################
# Introduction
################################################################################
The scripts in this directory are used to create RTL for the ESR slaves.
The list of registers is defined in CSV files. The code is automatically 
generated from there.

The file esr_slave_template.v is a template for the RTL of an ESR slave.
Edit this file and run udpate_template.py in order to update all the existing
ESR files with these changes. Any custom change per ESR should be placed inside
the CUSTOM PORTS|STATEMENTS|SIGNALS|POST_DECODE comments, or they will be lost

################################################################################
# code generation from csv
################################################################################

* Edit the reference CSV file:
   * CSV => esr.csv for main sheet, types/*.csv for type defintions

* Generate the new code:
python3 gen_esr_file.py

################################################################################
# xlsx file generation from csv
################################################################################

This command is to be used only when a new xlsx file has to be published.
Use command:

ssconvert --merge-to=<output_file_name>.xlsx esr.csv types/*.csv

If tool is not installed in your machine, you can find it in sc-vnc server.

Fancy colors, font selection, column width adjustment and other "decoration"
must be manually done. 

File Minion_ESR_Registers.xlsx has some color customization from the original 
raw conversion of CSV into esr_autogenerated.xlsx file.

################################################################################
Explanation of some of the columns of the spreadsheet:
################################################################################
Mod => what ESR sub-module this register corresponds to
PP => protection bits. 2 bits that will be prepended in the MSB of the address input port
Address, Name => register address and name
Access => RW or RO
Description => brief description of the register
Type => set to the register type for RTL (e.g. a struct).  If there is a sheet with the same name as the type, the scripts will create a struct with what you define there. Note that you can use structs or any other type (e.g. enums) that are not defined in the sheet
     => If set to MANUAL, the script will not create a register (if it is RW) but only decoding logic.  You'll have to handle it yourself
width => For logic vectors selects the width. If set to 0, the register is hardwired (there is no physical register). Note that 'Type' and 'width' fields are mutually exclusive, you cannot specify them both.
rdata => if not set, the read value is the contents of the craeted register; otherwise it returns the expression in this field. For shared regs returns the expression, for non-shared, returns expresion[thread]
wdata => if not set, write data directly from core... otherwise, the data written in the register is this expression
shadow => set if reg is a shadow (with less fields) of another register (possibily with more privileges). Writing and reading to this reg will manage the fields that are accessible (readable/writeable) automatically (the types must be defined in the sheet)
resetVal => if set (for RW regs), the CSR will have reset and this determines the initial value.
reset => Choose any of 'GLOBAL' (default), 'DEBUG' or 'NON-DEBUG' to reset with (reset, reset | reset_debug, reset|reset_non_debug) respectivelly
triggerCnt
latch => set to YES to implement with latches rather than FF
connect_to_port => will be connected to input port (RO) or output port (RW) with the name esr_NAME_op/ip
implemented => YES/NO. if set to NO, the row defining the reg will be ignored.
ifdef => if set to XXX, puts the register between ifdef XXX /endif blocks. Ignored if not set
comment


Regarding defining the structs,

fields/width: defines name/width of the fields [mandatory]. MSB left.
RO: optional. Set to YES if you want that field to be RO.
ROValue: optional. if field is RO, force an specific value.

other entries will be ignored

